🌐 Personal Portfolio Website
📌 Overview

This is my personal portfolio website built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
The purpose of this project is to showcase my skills, projects, and contact information in a clean and responsive format.

This project helps me practice frontend development fundamentals, responsive design, and basic JavaScript functionality.

🚀 Live Demo

👉 https://personal-portfolio-project-kohl.vercel.app/

✨ Features

Fully responsive design for all devices
Clean and simple UI layout
Navigation between different sections
Hover effects and basic animations
Contact form with simple validation
Organized and readable code structure

🛠️ Tech Stack

HTML5 – Structure
CSS3 – Styling, Flexbox, Grid, Media Queries
JavaScript – Basic interactivity and form validation
Git & GitHub – Version control
Vercel – Deployment

📁 Project Structure

personal-portfolio-project/
│
├── index.html # Main webpage
├── responsive.css # Styling file
├── script.js # JavaScript functionality
├── assets/ # Images and icons
└── README.md # Project documentation
⚙️ How to Run This Project

Follow these steps to run locally:

git clone https://github.com/Yashwanthkumar-dev/personal-portfolio-project.git

cd personal-portfolio-project

open index.html

🧪 Testing Performed

Tested responsiveness on mobile, tablet, and desktop
Verified form validation (empty and invalid inputs)
Checked navigation links across sections
Tested layout alignment in different screen sizes
Ensured cross-browser compatibility

🧠 Technical Details

This project is built using basic frontend concepts with a focus on responsiveness and clean structure.

The layout is created using HTML semantic elements like header, section, and footer
CSS Flexbox and Grid are used to arrange sections properly
Media Queries are added to make the website responsive for mobile, tablet, and desktop screens
Simple JavaScript DOM manipulation is used for form validation and basic interactions
The contact form checks for basic input validation like empty fields and correct email format
The website is deployed using Vercel for hosting

🧠 What I Learned

While building this project, I improved my understanding of:

Structuring a complete web page
Using Flexbox and Grid for layout design
Making websites responsive using media queries
Basic DOM manipulation using JavaScript
Deploying projects using Vercel

